'366' => q~Settings for New Member Notification E-mail~,
'367' => q~Notification e-mail for new member?<br /><span class="small">If checked, a notification concerning the registration of a new member will be sent to the e-mail address below.</span>~,
'368' => q~Notification e-mail address:<br /><span class='small'>If left blank, the e-mail will be sent to: {yabb webmaster_email}</span>~,
'371' => q~Current Forum Time~,
'371d' => q~Select Forum Time Zone:<br /><span class="small">Choose the country and city that represents your preferred default Time Zone.<br />If the only choices are UTC and 'local', you do not have the necessary Modules to use country/city based Time Zones. In that case, use 'local' and manually set your Forum Time Offset to set your Forum's Time difference from UTC, or choose UTC.</span>~,
'371a' => q~Enable Time Zone choices for Users:<br /><span class="small">If the necessary <strong>DateTime::TimeZone</strong> Perl Module is not installed, users will only be able to choose 'UTC'. If the forum default Time Zone is 'local' users will also have 'Forum Default Time Offset' as an option.</span>~,
'local' => q~local~,
'371e' => q~Enable DST using 'local' Forum Time Zone and Forum Time Offset (above).<br /><span class="small">This setting assumes your hosting server is in a Time Zone that uses the same dates for Daylight Savings Time as you want for your forum and is set to recognize its local time with DST. Otherwise choose UTC as your Time Zone or manually adjust for DST in your Time Zone using the 'Set Forum Time Offset'</span>.~,
'371f' => q~Set Forum Time Offset:<br /><span class="small">Adjust your forum's time difference from UTC here.</span>~,
'371b' => q~Enable the dynamic clock at the top of the page?~,
'371c' => q~Server Time Correction (in seconds +/-)~,
'372' => q~Number of Top Posters for Members List~,
'373' => q~Number of members displayed per page in Member List~,
'374' => q~Maximum Topics displayed per page in the Message Index~,
'375' => q~Maximum number of messages displayed per page of a Topic~,
'376' => q~Number of days after a post is made that it will no longer show as "new" in either the Board view or Message view.~,
'377' => q~Enable Spell Checking?<br /><span class="small">This spell checker relies on external websites belonging to GoogieSpell. You must take into consideration firewall settings and content blockers in using this feature.</span><br /><strong><span class="under">License:</span></strong><br />The scripts in /yabbfiles/googiespell are dual licensed. One is for free software ("open source") the other is for proprietary software.<br />The free license is <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/" target="_blank">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 3.0 license</a>. Under this license you can only use GoogieSpell with/in free software (i.e. software where the source is released). You cannot use GoogieSpell with proprietary software even if you do not distribute your software.<br />For more details see <a href="http://orangoo.com/labs/GoogieSpell/Buy_License/" target="_blank">orangoo.com/labs/GoogieSpell/Buy_License/</a>.~,
'377a' => q~If you see this message, some required Perl modules were not found.<br />If an error message like "Can't locate ..." is shown, then this module is not installed on your server.<br /><br />~,
'377b' => q~Installed~,
'377c' => q~<br />To use SpellChecker, you must have installed all of these modules on your server. Ask your server host to install them for you.<br />Please install:<br />- Bundle::LWP (for LWP::UserAgent and HTTP::Request::Common)<br />- Crypt::SSLeay~,
