'710' => q~Password-Strength-Meter Scores<br /><span class ="small">Here you can define when the line jumps to the next higher level. Default is <em>10,15,30,40</em>. <span style="color:red">Insert only numbers and commas or you can get into trouble.</span><br />Set to <em>-1,-1,-1,-1</em> to disable the Password-Strength-Meter feature. Then it will show only if the Password is too short or if it is OK.</span>~,
'711' => q~Password-Strength-Meter common words<br /><span class ="small">Enter all words that will be shown as "Unsafe Password.". The words must be between "" and separated by commas. Example:<br />"123456","abcdef","password"</span>~,
