'guestmedia' => q~Prevent Guests from seeing media files or having clickable auto-linked URLs in messages?~,
'guestlang' => q~Enable Guest language selection?~,
'checkspace' => q~Enabling this will allow you to set the various free disk space checks. Checking the free disk space is primarily a Linux function and may not work properly on Windows/IIS servers. The free disk space functions may return incorrect values when used on shared hosting services.~,
'checkspace2' => q~ (If the Free Disk Space Functions Utility page fails to load your server <strong>does not support those functions</strong>.)~,
'checkspclabel' => q~Advanced Settings - Free Disk Space Functions~,
'quota' => q~<em>quota</em>: Enabling this uses the Linux shell command 'quota' to check for free disk space. This is the preferred method to use. The checkbox will be disabled if this command is not available on your server.<br /><span class="small">If your available disk space drops below 100&thinsp;000 Bytes (100 KB), the forum will automatically go into Maintenance Mode to prevent running out of space and losing data.<br /><strong>Reminder</strong>: Only Admins can access the forum when in Maintenance Mode.</span>~,
'quota_value' => q~<em>quota</em>: Select the Filesystem your Forum is on:<br /><span class="small">The right Filesystem should be preselected if 'quota' was saved <em>disabled</em> before.</span>~,
'quotahostuser' => q~<em>quota</em>: Your username on your host server:<br /><span class="small">Should be pre-written. Available if the above is checked.</span>~,
'findtime' => q~<em>find</em>: Time between the Linux shell command 'find' checks file sizes in the directory you must insert below and its sub directories. This and the following two fields will be disabled if this command is not available on your server.<br />Set to 0 to be able to chose other checking method like 'quota' or free disk space checking.<br /><span class="small">Since this can be a very time-extensive job, you should insert a reasonable high value such as 300 (five hours) or 1440 (one day). Once the free host space is obtained after each 'find', this method is of very low server load.</span>~,
'findroot' => q~<em>find</em>: Path to the root directory of your user account on a multiple user host system.<br /><span class="small">The path must be <strong>from system root to your user root</strong>. Example:<br />/var/www/your_domain_name/<br />/var/www/web1234/<br /><br />You can also specify a path to your forum or a directory in your forum and specify a maximum amount of space as a limit for it 'find' will use that limit instead of your host account limits. Example:<br />/var/www/your_domain_name/cgi-bin/yabb2/<br />/var/www/your_domain_name/public_html/yabbfiles/Attachments/</span>~,
'findmax' => q~<em>find</em>: Available space you are allowed to use in the above directory (in Megabytes).<br /><span class="small">This should be the same amount of disk space as your hosting plan advertises.<br />Since you should set 'find' to check the available host space only all X hours or once per day, you should set this value lower than the space your host provides to you, to avoid running out of space due to some sudden increase of disk use for example by attachments or other high volume consuming postings.<br />To enable 'find' for free host space checking this value must be &gt; 0. If the used space within the above directory is higher than this value, the forum will automatically go into Maintenance Mode to prevent running out of space and losing data.<br /><strong>Reminder</strong>: Only Admins can access the forum when in Maintenance Mode.<br />Just in case you don't remember: 1 GB = 1024 MB</span>~,
'diskspacecheck' => q~Enable free disk space check?<br /><span class="small">This checks for the available physical disk space on the Linux or Windows server. Be aware that not all of that disk space may be usable by you. It may show a number greater than allowed by your personal hosting plan.<br />If your available disk space drops below 100&thinsp;000 Bytes (100 KB), the forum will automatically go into Maintenance Mode to prevent running out of space and losing data.<br />Reminder: Only Admins can access the forum when in Maintenance Mode.</span>~,
'getreversedns' => q~Enable Reverse DNS Lookup.~,
'minlinkpost' => q~Minimum number of posts a member must have before links and images can be posted~,
'minlinkpost_exp' => q~This prevents spambots from spamposting directly after registering~,
'minlinksig' => q~Number of posts a member must have before links and images can be created in signature~,
'minlinksig_exp' => q~This avoids spambots from creating spam-signatures directly after registering~,
'minlinkweb' => q~Number of posts a member must have before they can link to a website in their profile~,
'minlinkweb_exp' => q~This prevents spammers from linking to a website directly after registering~,
'stealth' => q~Enable 'Stealth' mode for Admins and Global Mods?<br /><span class="small">If checked, Admins and Global Mods will have the option not to appear "online" to any other Member Groups or Guests.<br />This will need to be enabled in User CP - Profile - Contact Information.</span>~,
'mlview' => q~Select the Member Groups allowed to view the Member List?~,
'buddylist' => q~Enable Buddy List?~,
'regreason' => q~Maximum allowed characters in user's "Reason(s) for Registering"~,
'showall' => q~Show "All" on page selectors and Topic Summary?~,
'imageinquote' => q~If checked, embedded images within posts will appear in quotes of those posts.<br /><span class="small">If disabled, images in quoted posts will be shown as links to the images.</span>~,
'extendedprofiles' => q~Use Extended Profiles?<br /><span class="small">If enabled, an additional item called "Profile Fields" will be shown in the sidebar to the left. There, you can add functions to the users' profiles.<br />Leave this unchecked if you don't use this feature to save server load.</span>~,
'forumnumbformat' => q~Select default number format:~,
'nospammer' => q~Send default e-mail to rejected users even when no reason is given when registration is by Admin approval. Check for 'yes'~,
'honeypot' => qq~Activate Honeypot Spambot catcher. Check for 'yes' (<a href="$boardurl/AdminIndex.$yyaext?action=honeypot">Edit Honeypot</a>)~,
'spamfruits' => q~Activate SpamFruits Spambot catcher. Check for 'yes'~,
'eventcal_set' => q~Event Calendar Settings~,
'eventcal_set1' => q~Edit your Event Calendar Settings~,
'calsplit' => q~Maximum number of birthdays shown on page.<br /><span class="small">Page will split into individual month displays. Leave blank or set to 0 to disable.</span>~,
'addtab_on' => q~Show Add and Edit Tabs on Forum?~,
'rules' => q~Board Rules~,
'rules1' => q~Enable Board Rules~,
'rules2' => q~Rules Title~,
'rules3' => q~Rules~,
'rules4' => q~You can use HTML here.~,
'iplookup' => q~Enable IP Lookup?<br /><span class="small">Checking this option will turn IP Addresses into active links allowing you to look them up on a Whois server.</span>~,
'iplookup_urls' => q~IP Lookup Whois Servers:<br /><span class="small">Here you can add or remove Whois servers to/from the IP Lookup page.<br />Use {ip} in the URL to substitute the actual IP address, and separate the title and URL with a pipe symbol '|'.<br />One URL per line. Spaces in the site name should be replaced by '_'.<br />Example: My_LookupSite|mylookupsite.com?ip={ip}</span>~,
'iplookup_protocols' => q~. Valid protocols are http and https.~,
'show_user_age' => q~Show User Age in Message View?~,
'show_reg_date' => q~Show User Registration Date in Message View?~,
'edit_gender_limit' => q~Set a limit on the amount of times that members can edit their gender:<br /><span class="small">1 = Cannot be edited after the first time it has been entered.<br />0 = No limit.</span>~,
'edit_age_limit' => q~Set a limit on the amount of times that members can edit their birthdate:<br /><span class="small">1 = Cannot be edited after the first time it has been entered.<br />0 = No limit.</span>~,
'min_reg_time' => q~Minimum amount of time in seconds which must be spent on the registration page:<br /><span class="small">This is to stop spambots which automatically fill in the registration form in a time which is humanly impossible.<br />Set to 0 to disable.</span>~,
